(279, 2, '2024-06-14 16:47:06', '2024-06-14 16:47:06', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ever since I was a kid, I have been fascinated with the magical world of Thumbelina, where the smallest things are just regular size and a girl can sleep in a flower. So I decided to create my own version of the visuals I have loved my entire life, keeping the whimsical and fairylike proportions and adding elements from my own childhood, like the long silver braids of my grandmother or the cattails on the water.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":252,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pulgarcita-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-252\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":253,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pulgarcita-2-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-253\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":254,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pulgarcita-3-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-254\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Thumbelina book spreads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '251-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 16:47:06', '2024-06-14 16:47:06', '', 251, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=279', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(280, 2, '2024-06-14 16:47:38', '2024-06-14 16:47:38', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I created a mini story that reminds us how bright and important friendship is when the wheather (or life) is a little cloudy. This illustrations are created as if they are part of an illustrated children\'s book, taking into account composition and text placement.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":171,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Pagina-1-y-2-eng-1024x640.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-171\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":173,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Pagina-3-y-4-eng-1024x640.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-173\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Friendship is like sunshine - pages', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '244-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 16:47:38', '2024-06-14 16:47:38', '', 244, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=280', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(281, 2, '2024-06-14 16:57:16', '2024-06-14 16:57:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is nothing like a handmade gift! I drew Polya Bulba\'s character Olivia as part of her Draw This In Your Style challenge, but decided to make a cute story out of it! Little Olivia decided to make a giant heart for her parents (almost as big as her love) and they absolutely loved it!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":277,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/IMG_1385-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-277\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":276,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/IMG_1422-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-276\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Big Heart - illustrations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '275-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 16:57:16', '2024-06-14 16:57:16', '', 275, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=281', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(282, 2, '2024-06-14 16:57:34', '2024-06-14 16:57:34', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The moon is the sun\'s little sister, when they finally meet, there is nothing quite like them. I made this illustration celebrating the solar eclipse on North America that filled everyone with wonder the past April 8th, I cannot help but think that this two celestial bodies are sisters who have their own beauty but create something special when they reunite. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":261,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/IMG_0283-819x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-261\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":262,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/IMG_0285-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-262\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Sun and Moon - illustrations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '260-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 16:57:34', '2024-06-14 16:57:34', '', 260, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=282', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(283, 2, '2024-06-14 16:57:48', '2024-06-14 16:57:48', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ever since I was a kid, I have been fascinated with the magical world of Thumbelina, where the smallest things are just regular size and a girl can sleep in a flower. So I decided to create my own version of the visuals I have loved my entire life, keeping the whimsical and fairylike proportions and adding elements from my own childhood, like the long silver braids of my grandmother or the cattails on the water.  </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":252,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pulgarcita-1-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-252\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":253,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pulgarcita-2-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-253\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":254,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Pulgarcita-3-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-254\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Thumbelina - book spreads', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '251-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 16:57:48', '2024-06-14 16:57:48', '', 251, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=283', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(284, 2, '2024-06-14 16:58:06', '2024-06-14 16:58:06', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As I am entering a new stage in my life, I wanted to take a step back and look inside, that´s how this illustration was born. Having a conversation with my younger self, who I want to make proud. I wanted to portray the conection that we share with our inner child, and how important it is to nurture and honor that relationship. Made in Procreate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":190,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_4118-1-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Cute illustration with a kid in a garden\" class=\"wp-image-190\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'We\'re on our own, kid - illustration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '247-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 16:58:06', '2024-06-14 16:58:06', '', 247, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=284', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(285, 2, '2024-06-14 17:13:13', '2024-06-14 17:13:13', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What wonders can we find on the cherry tree? Illustration I made exploring the relationship kids have with nature. I wanted it to feel magical and full of wonder, showing the astonishment of discovering the world for the first time. I included some color tests I made before choosing the warm pink palette. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":237,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_6958-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-237\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":238,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_6875-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-238\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":239,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_6873-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-239\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":240,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_6874-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-240\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Cherry tree wonders - illustration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '236-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 17:13:13', '2024-06-14 17:13:13', '', 236, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=285', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(286, 2, '2024-06-14 17:13:33', '2024-06-14 17:13:33', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>What did you wanted to do when you grew up as a little kid? I asked this question to my friends and I got a deal of heart-warming answers. From wildlife photographer to mermaid, this illustration pictures every posibility that is at our reach when we are kids and our imagination knows no limits. Showing a younger version of myself sorrounded by a representation of my friend\'s answers, this illustration is a celebration of children\'s creative potential.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":226,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_0346-1-1024x1024.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-226\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'When I grow up... - illustration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '225-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 17:13:33', '2024-06-14 17:13:33', '', 225, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=286', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(287, 2, '2024-06-14 17:13:55', '2024-06-14 17:13:55', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A series I did for a project titled \"Here I am: women in art history\" which I developed as part of my art history course at University. The objective of this project is to retrieve spaces and recognition that was taken away from women throughout art history. The artists portrayed are Remedios Varo, Sofonisba Anguissola and Mary Cassat respectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":221,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_0225-1-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-221\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":222,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_0224-1-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-222\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":223,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/IMG_0223-1-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-223\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Here I am... Women in art history - chapter book illustrations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 17:13:55', '2024-06-14 17:13:55', '', 220, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=287', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(288, 2, '2024-06-14 17:14:25', '2024-06-14 17:14:25', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Illustration made for \"Casa Cler\'s \" 2022 planner. For the October cover I wanted to illustrate something that captured the magic and coziness of this season, so I decided to bring this character to life! A little witch that enjoys flying at night.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":183,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/IMG_0037-1-1024x658.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-183\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'October flight -calendar illustration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '61-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 17:14:25', '2024-06-14 17:14:25', '', 61, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=288', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(289, 2, '2024-06-14 17:14:40', '2024-06-14 17:14:40', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nita has a day ahead full of adventures! In these illustrations we follow Nita the frog on her day in Guanajuato city, the city of frogs!. As the day goes by Nita visits iconic landmarks of the city, the day ending with her tucked in bed as the city glows at night. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":177,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/IMG_1841-1-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-177\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":178,\"width\":819,\"height\":819,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/IMG_1840-1-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-178\" style=\"width:819px;height:819px\" width=\"819\" height=\"819\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":179,\"width\":819,\"height\":819,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/IMG_1842-1-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-179\" style=\"width:819px;height:819px\" width=\"819\" height=\"819\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":180,\"width\":819,\"height\":1024,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/IMG_1839-1-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-180\" style=\"width:819px;height:1024px\" width=\"819\" height=\"1024\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":181,\"width\":820,\"height\":1026,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/IMG_1838-1-819x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-181\" style=\"width:820px;height:1026px\" width=\"820\" height=\"1026\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'A day with Nita - illustrations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '58-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-06-14 17:14:40', '2024-06-14 17:14:40', '', 58, 'https://marianagutierrezillustration.com/?p=289', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
